Dear TIM students, alumni, staff, and faculty engaged in "Up Our Game, Cana=
da!"
Let=92s start with a challenge: strive to be better today than you were yes=
terday. That=92s how we grow=97by staying committed, staying focused, and l=
earning to navigate the volatility, uncertainty, complexity, and ambiguity =
around us.
To support your efforts, I=92m sharing two important documents:

  *
Descriptions for 11 of the 12 building blocks of Up Our Game, Canada! (Stru=
cture & Assignments file)
These include: Team, About, Key Aspects, April 28 Objective, and April 28 D=
eliverables=97plus who is currently assigned to each element.
  *
An example of improvement tips (Tips for producing videos using HeyGen file=
)
This sample document (focused on video production) offers tips for strength=
ening an element. I=92d like each team to create a similar tips document fo=
r their element by April 28.

Here=92s what I need from you now:

  1.
Review both documents carefully and send me your suggestions or recommended=
 changes (including changing teams)
  2.
Confirm who will lead each of the 11 teams we have launched.

Thanks for the energy and focus you=92re bringing to this initiative. Let=
=92s keep raising our game and building momentum=97together.
If you have questions, need additional information, or need to brainstorm, =
please contact me.
Best,
Tony B.


